meta.educational_goal: Understand the operations of a deque data structure.

states.label: Idle
Item Pushed Front
evidence: button.onclick = function() { const item = prompt('Enter a value to push front:', ''); if (item) deque.pushFront(item); input.value = item; };

states.label: Item Pushed Back
evidence: button2.onclick = function() { const item = prompt('Enter a value to push back:', ''); if (item) deque.pushBack(item); input.value = item; };

states.label: Item Popped Front
evidence: button3.onclick = function() { const item = deque.popFront(); input.value = item; };

states.label: Item Popped Back
evidence: button4.onclick = function() { const item = deque.popBack(); input.value = item; };

states.label: Item Peeked Front
evidence: button5.onclick = function() { const item = deque.peekFront(); input.value = item; };

states.label: Item Peeked Back
evidence: button6.onclick = function() { const item = deque.peekBack(); input.value = item; };

states.label: Deque Emptied
evidence: button7.onclick = function() { deque = new Deque(); input.value = ''; };
